# Cursor Rules for ApolloCRM (dealerwyze-app)

## Project Overview
- **Product:** DealerWyze (multi-tenant CRM) + RealtyWyze (real estate agent CRM)
- **Stack:** Next.js 16, TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, Supabase, Twilio, Stripe
- **One codebase, two verticals:** Code routes by domain (dealerwyze.com vs realtywyze.us)
- **Status:** v1.1 hardening complete (2026-06-08)

## Repository Structure
```
dealerwyze-app/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router
│   ├── api/               # API routes (always org-scoped)
│   ├── (dealer)/          # Dealer-specific pages
│   └── (realtor)/         # Real estate agent pages
├── lib/
│   ├── auth/              # Authentication & authorization
│   ├── supabase/          # Database & RLS
│   ├── rateLimit/         # Rate limiting (fail-closed design)
│   ├── sms/               # Twilio SMS integration
│   ├── audit/             # Audit logging
│   ├── vehicles/          # Dealer vehicle logic
│   ├── properties/        # RE property logic
│   └── ai/                # AI integrations (Claude, Gemini, Groq)
├── components/            # Reusable UI components
├── supabase/
│   ├── migrations/        # Database migrations
│   └── rls/              # Row-level security policies
├── DEPLOY.md             # Deployment workflows
├── GIT_STRUCTURE.md      # Git & Vercel setup
└── STAGING_PRODUCTION_SETUP.md

Related repo:
dealerwyze-strategy/     # Planning, research, roadmap (read-only for code context)
```

## Critical Architecture Rules

### 1. Multi-Tenancy & Security
- **ALWAYS** scope all queries to authenticated `org_id`
- Never trust `org_id` from request body — derive from `requireProfile()`
- Use `createClient()` for org-scoped routes (RLS enforced)
- Use `createServiceClient()` ONLY in: platform admin, crons, webhooks, auth flows
- If using `createServiceClient()`, add explicit `.eq('org_id', ...)` filter on every query

### 2. Rate Limiting (v1.1 Hardening)
- **Fail-closed design:** Returns 429 when Upstash unavailable, never silent-allow
- Rate limiters wired into all SMS delivery paths (sequences, direct send, auto-response)
- Check `lib/rateLimit/upstash.ts` for fallback behavior
- SMS limit: 20 per 5 minutes per org
- CSV import limit: 5 per hour per org

### 3. Vertical Isolation
- Code supports two verticals: `'dealer'` and `'real_estate'`
- **Backend enforcement:** CSV import, Monroney extract, property import all check `org.vertical` and return 403 for non-matching
- UI-only gating is NOT sufficient — backend must validate
- Vertical routing in code via domain (dealerwyze.com routes to dealer, realtywyze.us to agent)

### 4. Audit Logging
- High-risk actions logged via `writeAuditLog()` from `lib/audit/log.ts`
- Logged areas: impersonation, payments, exports, settings changes, webhook auth failures
- Each log includes `source` field (paste/csv/auction) and `vehicle_state` field for imports
- Audit table is append-only (no UPDATE/DELETE)

### 5. API Design
- All org routes: `POST /api/...` with `requireProfile()` first
- All rate-limited routes: Check limiter BEFORE business logic
- All public/webhook routes: Validate signatures & replay resistance
- Error responses: Never expose other orgs' IDs, internal errors, or stack traces
- Use proper HTTP status codes (429 for rate limit, 403 for permission, 404 for not found)

## Deployment & Environments

### Git Branches
- **develop:** Staging code → pushed to staging.dealerwyze.com
- **main:** Production code → pushed to dealerwyze.com + realtywyze.us
- **feature/*:** Feature branches PR'd into develop first

### Vercel Projects
- **dealer-wyze:** Production, main branch, auto-deploys
- **dealer-wyze-staging:** Staging, develop branch, auto-deploys

### Deploy Scripts
```bash
./deploy-staging.sh    # Deploys develop to staging
./deploy-prod.sh       # Deploys main to production (requires confirmations)
```

## Common Tasks

### Create a New API Endpoint
1. File: `app/api/[path]/route.ts`
2. Start with: `const profile = await requireProfile()`
3. Scope all queries: `.eq('org_id', profile.org_id)`
4. If rate-limited: Check limiter before business logic
5. If high-risk: Call `writeAuditLog()` after success

### Add Feature to Both Verticals
- Code once in `/lib`, import in both `(dealer)` and `(realtor)` routes
- Use `org.vertical` checks for vertical-specific logic
- Test on both dealerwyze.com AND realtywyze.us

### Deploy to Production
```bash
git checkout main && git pull
./deploy-prod.sh    # Double-confirmed, safe to use
```

## Testing
- Unit tests: `npm test` (required before deploy)
- Build: `npm run build` (required before deploy)
- Local dev: `npm run dev` (test at http://localhost:3000)
- Staging: Always test on staging.dealerwyze.com before production
- Production: Verify both dealerwyze.com + realtywyze.us respond

## Linting & Quality
- ESLint: `npx eslint app lib components`
- TypeScript: `npm run build` includes type-checking
- Prettier: Configured in `.prettierrc`
- No secrets in code (use Vercel env vars)

## Performance & Optimization
- Rate limiting prevents abuse
- Export pagination limits 10k rows per page (prevents timeouts)
- Cursor-based pagination for large datasets
- No N+1 queries (use joins where possible)
- Cache where appropriate (Redis via Upstash)

